sequenceDiagram
    actor "External User" as ExternalUser
    participant "Frontend SPA" as FrontendSPA
    participant "Backend API" as BackendAPI
    participant "PostgreSQL DB" as PostgreSQLDB
    participant "AWS Cognito" as AWSCognito

    ExternalUser->>FrontendSPA: 1. Clicks unique registration link from invitation email (e.g., /register?token=...)
    FrontendSPA-->>ExternalUser: Registration page is rendered
    activate BackendAPI
    FrontendSPA->>BackendAPI: 2. GET /api/v1/user-invitations/{token}
    BackendAPI-->>FrontendSPA: 200 OK { email: '...' } | 404 Not Found | 410 Gone (Expired) | 409 Conflict (Used)
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDB: 3. SELECT * FROM UserInvitations WHERE Token = @token
    PostgreSQLDB-->>BackendAPI: Invitation record or NULL
    BackendAPI->>BackendAPI: 4. Validate token: Check existence, expiry (createdAt + lifespan), and usage (usedAt IS NULL)
    BackendAPI-->>BackendAPI: Validation result (Valid/Expired/Used/Not Found)
    ExternalUser->>FrontendSPA: 5. Submits registration form with name and strong password
    FrontendSPA->>BackendAPI: 6. POST /api/v1/user-invitations/{token}/activate
    BackendAPI-->>FrontendSPA: 200 OK | 400 Bad Request (Password Invalid) | 4xx (Token Invalid) | 502 Bad Gateway (Cognito Failure)
    BackendAPI->>BackendAPI: 7. [Security Checkpoint] Re-validate token and password complexity rules
    BackendAPI-->>BackendAPI: Validation result or exception
    BackendAPI->>BackendAPI: 8. [Security Checkpoint] Hash password using Argon2id algorithm (REQ-NFR-003)
    BackendAPI-->>BackendAPI: Hashed password string
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDB: 9. BEGIN TRANSACTION
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDB: 10. UPDATE Users SET Status='Active', HashedPassword=@hash, Name=@name WHERE Id=@userId
    PostgreSQLDB-->>BackendAPI: Rows affected
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDB: 11. UPDATE UserInvitations SET UsedAt=NOW() WHERE Token=@token
    PostgreSQLDB-->>BackendAPI: Rows affected
    BackendAPI->>AWSCognito: 12. [Integration Point] Call AdminConfirmSignUp API
    AWSCognito-->>BackendAPI: 200 OK | AWS SDK Exception
    BackendAPI->>PostgreSQLDB: 13. COMMIT TRANSACTION
    BackendAPI->>BackendAPI: 14. [Audit Requirement] Log 'User Activated' event
    FrontendSPA->>ExternalUser: 15. Redirect to login page with a success message

    note over BackendAPI: The initial GET request to validate the token is a UX enhancement. It prevents the user from fill...
    note over BackendAPI: Failure of the AWS Cognito call is a critical failure path. The system must roll back all local d...

    deactivate BackendAPI
